If $\Phi(h,g)\ne 0$, then there exists $x\in G$ such that $g^{-1}x=:b_1\in B_1$ and $xh^{-1}=:b_2\in B_2$,
    so $h=b_2^{-1}g b_1 \in B_2^{-1}g B_1$.
    By using the unimodularity of $G$, we deduce
    \begin{align}
        \Phi(h,g) &= \int_G \varphi_1(g^{-1}x) \overline{\varphi_2(xb_1^{-1}g^{-1}b_2)}\left({\delta(g^{-1}x)}{\delta(xh^{-1})}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}} \dif x\nonumber\\
