The \emph{uniform decay} exponent $\thetagh$ is defined to be the infimum of $\theta \in [0,1]$ such that for all $f_1,f_2\in \Cc(G/H)$, there exists a constant $C>0$ such that uniformly for all $g\in G$, we have
    \begin{equation*}
        \Modofinner{\lambdagh(g)f_1, f_2} \leq C \bigexp{2(\theta-1)\rho\kappa(g)},
    \end{equation*}
    where the map $\kappa: G\to \alie^+$ is the Cartan projection to the positive Weyl chamber $\alie^+$ of a Cartan subspace $\alie$ of $\glie$, and the linear form $\rho: \alie\to \bbR$ is the half sum of positive restricted roots of $(\alie; \glie)$. This number does not depend on the choice of the Cartan decomposition of $G$.

For a discrete subgroup $\Gamma$, the exponent $\theta_{G/\Gamma}$ is related to the number $\theta\!\left(\Ltwoggamma\right)$ defined in \cite[\S 1]{lutsko-weich2024polyhedral} via
    \begin{equation*}
        \theta\!\left(\Ltwoggamma\right) = \maxof{2\theta_{G/\Gamma} - 1 ,\, 0}.
    \end{equation*}

The \emph{optimal integrability} exponent $p_{G/H}$ of the homogeneous space $G/H$ is defined by the infimum of $p\in[1,\infty]$ such that for any compact subset $B$ of $G/H$, we have
    \begin{equation*}
        \Innerprod{\lambda_{G/H}(\cdot)\indicator_{B}, \indicator_{B}} \in \Lspace^p(G).
    \end{equation*}

[\autoref{def: relative exponent of closed subgroups}]
    The \emph{volume growth} exponent $\deltagh$ of $H$ inside $G$ is defined by
    \begin{equation*}
        \deltagh := \maxde{0,\,\sup_{B\Subset G} \limsup_{g\to \infty} \frac{\log \nuh{H\cap BgB}}{\log \nug{BgB}}},
    \end{equation*}
    where $B$ ranges over compacta of nonempty interior, the measure $\nu_G$ is the Haar measure on $G$, and $\dif \nu_H(h) = \left(\det\Ad_{H}h\right)^{1/2} \dif h$ is the symmetric measure on $H$ (cf.\,\autoref{subsec: measures on homogeneous spaces}). This number equals the abscissa of convergence for the following analogue of Dirichlet series (cf.\,\autoref{prop: deltagh as the abscissa of convergence})
    \begin{equation*}
        [0,\infty] \ni t \longmapsto \int_H e^{-2t\rho\kappa(h)} \dif\nu_H(h).
    \end{equation*}

